reviewText: If you love makeup and would like to know how to use various products that you might not be familiar with, this video is for you. Styles with cosmetics change all the time, but this series of demonstrations are basic and very clearly explained and shown. I loved the way the artist used the beauty blender in a rolling fashion. So, even if you've been wearing makeup for years, there are still tips you can pick up here. It's also just so much fun to watch her at work, and I'll be watching this a few times and sharing with friends.
This video was really  detailed and great for learning to do basic make tips
Her own make up looks caked on why would I follow her advice. Her attitude is horrible she should at least seem happy or interested .

A makeup artist who blows on brushes? First definite no no. Contamination. Lip liner always. Lip color will last so much longer. Contour was weak. No highlighting.  And yes, I may not be Hollywood, but I'm a #mua.

She did have a lot of good pointers, mainly in the face routine like foundation and blush. But I am more interested in learning how to find and match the right skin tones and undertones. I really think it is a great video for complete beginners. Any one else that has some knowledge you might find yourself a little bored.
Good ideas. Make up styles change frequently.
I got this video for a few of my friends who are just learning about make-up and they loved it.... DEF. a GREAT buy!!!
